properties.areaDesc: Lake Michigan from Charlevoix to Point Betsie MI 5NM Offshore to mid lake; Lake Michigan from Rock Island Passage to Sturgeon Bay WI 5NM offshore to mid lake
properties.headline: Gale Warning issued January 10 at 2:43AM CST until January 12 at 2:00AM CST by NWS Milwaukee/Sullivan WI
properties.description:
* WHAT...Northeast winds 25 to 35 kt with gusts up to 40 kt and
waves 7 to 12 feet expected.

* WHERE...Lake Michigan from Charlevoix to Point Betsie MI 5NM
Offshore to mid lake and Lake Michigan from Rock Island
Passage to Sturgeon Bay WI 5NM offshore to mid lake.

* WHEN...From 10 PM this evening to 2 AM CST Sunday.

* IMPACTS...Strong winds will cause hazardous waves which could
capsize or damage vessels and reduce visibility.
properties.instruction:
Mariners should alter plans to avoid these hazardous conditions.
Remain in port, seek safe harbor, alter course, and/or secure the
vessel for severe conditions.

NWSheadline: GALE WARNING IN EFFECT FROM 10 PM THIS EVENING TO 2 AM CST SUNDAY
